🌿 PlantPro Backend
Welcome to the backend of PlantPro – an AI-powered plant care assistant that offers real-time disease detection, personalized care recommendations, and smart automation to help plants thrive effortlessly.

 Features
🌱 User Management: Registration, login, and authentication
📷 Plant Identification: AI-driven image recognition to identify plant species
🦠 Disease Detection: Real-time plant health analysis using machine learning models
📊 Care Recommendations: Personalized watering, sunlight, and temperature needs
🔔 Smart Notifications: Automated reminders and care alerts
💾 Data Storage: Secure cloud storage of user and plant data

🛠 Tech Stack
Language: Python (FastAPI / Flask / Django)
Database: PostgreSQL / MongoDB
AI/ML: TensorFlow / PyTorch for plant and disease detection
Cloud: AWS S3 / Firebase / Azure for image storage and hosting
Authentication: JWT / OAuth 2.0
API Testing: Postman / Swagger UI

⚙️ Installation
bash
Copy code
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/plantpro-backend.git
cd plantpro-backend

# 2. Create virtual environment and activate
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Run server
uvicorn main:app --reload  # (If using FastAPI)


plantpro-backend/
│
├── app/
│   ├── models/            # ML models
│   ├── routes/            # API routes
│   ├── services/          # Business logic
│   ├── utils/             # Helper functions
│   └── main.py            # Entry point
│
├── database/              # DB setup
├── tests/                 # Unit tests
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md


🧠 AI Models
Trained CNN models for plant and disease classification
Performance metrics: ~92% accuracy on test dataset
Real-time inference integrated via REST API

🛡 Security
Password hashing (bcrypt)
Token-based authentication (JWT)
Secure CORS and HTTPS support

